  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "After crossing the Rubicon Primaris and receiving both Guilliman's rebuke and the God-Emperor's vision, High Marshal Helbrecht is called to Hevaran, a ruined shrine world forbidden to rebuild. There, with only a small company of chosen Templars, he hunts a relic of Rogal Dorn and faces an ancient enemy shaped to test more than his sword arm. The quest is intimate by Black Templars standards, stripped of crusade-pageantry until faith, wrath, and self-image stand exposed. Pilgrimage, penance, and war fold into one march across sacred desolation.",
